s were slaveholders? No one wants to be told they have villainy in their genes."), mdx("p", null, "I\u2019m glad the nation is facing a racial reckoning, bigger than any in my lifetime. I can\u2019t imagine an entire race carrying the burden of a tragic past and a tragic present. The hardest part for me is staying hopeful and staying engaged. The more I age, the more I realize how slow the gears of change move. And it\u2019s working against us! Just so much bad shit is happening each day, it feels like even if the world could be in agreement about the horror that is happening and what they\u2019ll do to fix it, it\u2019ll be so late. So late. That\u2019s the best-case scenario. "), mdx("p", null, "I\u2019m waiting for the cultural revolution to come tomorrow! But it won\u2019t, and I know it. It just feels like I have no say in any of it anymore."));
